<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aignon, Yorou &amp; Ryberg" authorityYear="2021" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Inosperma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Inosperma africanum" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="africanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Inosperma africanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nested in 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Inosperma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Inosperma" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Inosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and indicated as sister to the rest of the genus in our phylogenetic analyses and is very distinct by its small size and a vinaceous to red pileus. It has a wide distribution in West Africa.
</paragraph>
